In .NET 10 (targeting Android 15+), apps run **edge-to-edge by default**, which means `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` no longer reshapes your layout. You need to react to **window insets** instead.

## Recommended approach

**1. Keep `adjustResize` in your AndroidManifest.xml:**
```xml
<activity android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize" ... />
```

**2. Add bottom padding that responds to the IME inset.** In your `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Listen for IME (keyboard) inset changes
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
            Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!,
            new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use the larger of IME or nav-bar bottom inset
            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
            view.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

**3. Your XAML stays normal** — no special wrappers needed:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" ... />

    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

## Why this works

| .NET 9 | .NET 10 (Android 15+) |
|---|---|
| `AdjustResize` shrinks the window | Window stays full-screen (edge-to-edge) |
| Layout auto-repositions | You must read IME insets and apply padding |

The `WindowInsetsCompat` listener fires whenever the keyboard opens/closes, pushing your input bar above it via bottom padding. This is the same pattern Google now recommends for native Android.

> **Tip:** If you also target iOS, it already handles this correctly via `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` — no extra code needed on that platform.
